# Done-Gate

**This file is yours.** `rasa.module.tasks` ships the portable task
lifecycle (`.claude/task-rules.md`), but it deliberately does not decide
what *done* means in your domain — that is the one thing that varies.
This file is where you define it.

A task leaves `active/` for `completed/` only when **both** hold:

1. every acceptance criterion in the task spec is met and verified, and
2. **every gate below passes.**

Each gate must be **objectively checkable** — a command that exits zero,
a named reviewer's approval, a produced document — never a feeling.
Never bypass a gate to ship faster.

---

## Gates (EDIT THIS)

> Replace the default below with your domain's real gates. Until you do,
> the minimum honest bar applies: acceptance criteria checked **and** a
> second party has reviewed and approved. Running on the default is a
> smell, not a destination.

- [ ] **Acceptance criteria** — every checklist item in the task spec is
      satisfied and individually verified.
- [ ] **Independent review** — a second party (not the author) has
      reviewed the work and approved.

---

## Examples — delete the ones you don't need

> Pick the block that matches your domain, paste its gates above, and
> tune them. These are illustrative, not prescriptive.

### Software domain (`rasa.domain.code`)

```markdown
- [ ] Build — `<project build command>` succeeds with no new warnings.
- [ ] Verification suite — `<project test command>` passes headless.
- [ ] Local run — the implemented flow boots and works.
- [ ] No console / log errors on the affected paths.
- [ ] PR opened with task link, acceptance checklist, and verification output.
```

### Legal domain (`rasa.domain.legal`)

```markdown
- [ ] Conflict check cleared for the matter.
- [ ] Cite-check / authority verification complete.
- [ ] Privilege and confidentiality handling confirmed.
- [ ] Supervising attorney review and sign-off.
- [ ] Filing-deadline / docketing requirements satisfied.
```

### Health domain (`rasa.domain.health`)

```markdown
- [ ] Clinical-rule validation passes for the affected pathway.
- [ ] PHI handling reviewed (no leakage; audit trail intact).
- [ ] Compliance / regulatory sign-off recorded.
- [ ] Clinical reviewer approval.
```

### Writing domain (`rasa.domain.writer`)

```markdown
- [ ] Continuity check against the bible (characters, timeline, canon).
- [ ] Voice / style pass against the project's voice ledger.
- [ ] Editorial review and approval.
```

---

## Enforcement note

How you *enforce* "every change is task-linked" is also domain-specific
and belongs here or in your `.claude/<domain>-task-rules.md`: a software
domain may wire a pre-commit `task-guard` hook; a domain whose changes
are document revisions enforces it at its own checkpoint. The rule holds
either way (see `.claude/task-rules.md` → "Every change is task-linked").
